r longer waiting times). (6) The wall-to-wall time distribution obeys double\npower laws with the break point at 60 minutes (corresponding to the correlation\nlength). (7) The small-scale magnetic flux ropes tend to accumulate near the\nheliospheric current sheet (HCS). The entire database is available at\n\\url{http://fluxrope.info} and in machine readable format in this article.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Oct 2018 14:50:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-28"}
